in this elements game, we explore space as the fundamental bedrock. and because there is a bad rock, we don't need to ponder what may exist outside of it, because everything that exists inside of it, is real. this is in some way connected to the concept of theory space in the y or universe.

and so space is represented as like the base. you could see it as a empty void or a blank white canvas, it's essentially formless infinity. and it's actually very therapeutic the way we choose to portray it in our universe. it's almost like a sensory deprivation tank, but we need to be careful not to romanticize the void because for some minds, they tend to think of death as a void and we don't want to romanticize that. 

so the element game begins in space, formless Infinity as matter, and the next part of the game is unlocked when you learn time. because once you have space and time, that gives birth to the emergence of Chaos and order and force and momentum and mass and the laws of physics and eventually the rest of the game is born from this starting space.